      "writtenOn": "2020-03-26T14:20:15Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "My rule of thumb is to use splat() for values you could write out as a literal in onProgram(), and use uniforms for anything else.  Since these are derived from fConfig, they make sense to me as uniforms.\n\nThere\u0027s very little downside to using uniforms.  The program should be correct either way, and uniforms allow for better caching.  splats in turn just allow for better constant propagation.",
